7f483e5f-7f5f-485b-a4e0-febacdde526d.2ff59514-95f8-4cdd-9e9e-21ab7118470e.prompt=Enter a value for directory 7f483e5f-7f5f-485b-a4e0-febacdde526d.33058951-61d8-42ec-9f3a-621625492d2b.prompt=Enter a value for suffix 7f483e5f-7f5f-485b-a4e0-febacdde526d.368d09f2-e303-42de-bfbf-9aac2072d321.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

7f483e5f-7f5f-485b-a4e0-febacdde526d.3e207e44-3a47-4271-9c2c-1145958fbe8c.prompt=Enter a value for suffix 7f483e5f-7f5f-485b-a4e0-febacdde526d.50794e27-7d78-4d8b-b86f-520533bb3f93.description=
Writes the data from "contents" input to the requested file. The operation can be used to overwrite existing content of the file,  append extra lines to it or even create a new file.

Input Parameters\:
file                - Full path to file (can be a UNC path, will attempt to create directory structure). If the file does not exist it is created first.
contents       - The contents to write to the file. Contents can have a new line delimiter which is also given as input to the operation, but it is optional. Example\: "This is line no. 01\nThis is line no. 2\n" where \n is the delimiter.
user              - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host for this operation.
password      - Password for the user.
delimiter        - Specifies the newline delimiter (\n, \r\n, etc) that is used for the "contents" input.
overwrite      - Specifies whether to overwrite the file or append to it. By default, the used value is true. Accepted values\: true, false or the empty string. If this is left empty, the file will be overwritten.
characterSet - The character encoding used to write to the file. The default is UTF-8. Example values\: windows-1252, UTF-16, UTF-16BE,  ISO-8859-1, US-ASCII, Shift_JIS etc.

Responses\:
success - The contents were written to the file.
failure - The operation did not succeed in writing the contents to file.
7f483e5f-7f5f-485b-a4e0-febacdde526d.5246352f-2f36-4ebb-8b67-ec6c9b89c32b.description=
Performs a XSL Transformation on a RAS to transform a XML document.  Runtime parameters can be specified with the paramKey and paramValue inputs.

Input Parameters\:
templateLocation - The location of the XSL stylesheet to use.  Can be a local file path or an http url.
xmlLocation - The location of the XML document to transform.  Can be a local file path or an http url.  This is optional because some stylesheets do not need a XML document and can create output based on runtime parameters.
outputFile - The local file to write the output of the transformation.  If an output file is not specified the output of the transformation will returned as returnResult.
paramKey - A list of parameter names delimited by paramDelimiter.
paramValue - A list of parameter values delimited by paramDelimiter.
paramDelimiter - List delimiter for paramKey and paramValue inputs (default is comma).

Responses\:
success - The XSL transformation succeeded.
failure - The XSL transformation failed.  See returnResult for failure reasons.

Results\:
returnResult - The output of the transformation if no output file is specified.

Notes\:
Specifying parameters\:
If more then one parameter needs to be specified for a transformation, populate paramKey with a list of parameter names and paramValue with the respective parameter values.  As an example here is a simple stylesheet that has parameters firstName, lastName and color (it does not transform an xml document)\:



OO
User
\#000000






Hello  \!



		




By default (with no parameters specified) this will create a html document that says\: "Hello OO User\!" in black text.  When you apply the following paramKey and paramValue inputs\:

paramKey\=firstName,lastName,color
paramValue\=Valued,Customer,blue
paramDelimiter\=,

The output with these parameters would create a html document that says\: "Hello Valued Customer\!" in blue text.

Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Inputs\:
    field1 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field2 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field3 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field4 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of  "field1" as it was specified at input or when filtered. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.

staticBinding.value: <!-- This template copies and renames ${keyTag} to ${valueTag} --> <xsl:template match="${keyTag}"> <${valueTag}> <xsl:apply-templates/> </${valueTag}> </xsl:template>

<?xml version="1.0"?> <xsl:stylesheet version="1.0" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform"> <xsl:output method="xml" version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" indent="yes"/>
<xsl:template match="@* | node()"> <xsl:copy> <xsl:apply-templates select="@* | node()"/> </xsl:copy> </xsl:template>
${xslt}
</xsl:stylesheet>

step.name: Write XSL to file (removing top 3 tags)

<?xml version="1.0"?> <xsl:stylesheet version="1.0" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform"> <xsl:output method="xml" version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" indent="yes"/>
!-- Removes the first three tags --> <xsl:template match="//Envelope/Body/node()|@*"> <xsl:copy-of select="node()" /> </xsl:template>
</xsl:stylesheet>
